<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vulgarr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've been trying for several weeks now to try and purchase Mark of Karn, but with no success. I've heard that it drops in Seb doing Jugs and also in Skyfire.<P>Are these the only 2 places to try and get this spell?<P>Also, should I be overly concerned about getting it in the first place?  I'm holding onto 10k for it just in case.<P>Thanks. <P>Vulgarr<BR>55th Templar, Cazic Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zygote</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>its unlikely you'll be able to buy it. Generally speaking if someone gets mark of karn it will go to a guild cleric. and it'll probably be alot more than 10k. <P>other than skyfire and juggs, I know it drops off of Korocust in Chardok. <P>Skyfire is probably your best bet, if you can find a couple people, preferably someone who can track, then you can pull named spawns which drop 51-58 spells. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vulgarr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I finally got lucky and had someone I knew sell it to me.  I bought it for 10k (on Cazic Thule).<P>I'm wondering if anyone has any strategies they like to use with it, aside from just casting it on the mob as soon as possible.  I'm becoming quickly aware of certain mobs MR, as sometimes, this spell just won't stick.<P>I think it's odd that I've gotten this spell before celestial healing.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Got mine for 750pp from a necro who got it in Skyfire. First time I have ever seen it sold though and I'd been looking for a while. It is definitely not worth 10k, it's a novelty at best and a waste of mana at worst - on par with the summonned hammer pet. Anything worth sticking it on is likely to be magic immune.<P>For celestial healing spend some time in the kobold areas of Velk's Lab and it is certain to drop for you.<p>[This message has been edited by Jubal (edited 06-19-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
